{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"e459da97649d642110890337cc621e34b3e08ab4529432f83ef089b26a848460","slug":"seismology.intro","location":"/seismology/intro.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"简介","content_includes_title":false,"github":"https://github.com/seismo-learn/seismology101","numbering":{"title":{"offset":1}},"source_url":"https://github.com/seismo-learn/seismology101/blob/main/source/seismology/intro.md","edit_url":"https://github.com/seismo-learn/seismology101/edit/main/source/seismology/intro.md","thumbnail":"/seismology101/build/seismology-overview-1c7d035e9da8af0a5def3275b8e9ff32.jpg","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"intro.md","url":"/seismology101/build/intro-c43073426e0095be7e1ab87ff92c61b9.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":6,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"本节贡献者: {{姚家园}}、{{田冬冬}}","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"h9r4Tcyt61"}],"key":"HI7OQJSUeS"}],"key":"EryJbYrDTc"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1},"end":{"line":4,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"最近更新日期: 2021-10-28","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1},"end":{"line":4,"column":1}},"key":"ThYLUGV32q"}],"key":"Fv4ItFQFEs"}],"key":"L5qFArwZlb"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":6,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"预计阅读时间: 10 分钟","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"xDEUWlutt6"}],"key":"ESx0ZPH2zG"}],"key":"IeaSGMz9R0"}],"key":"RX3oTfNcbh"},{"type":"thematicBreak","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"ZWimeX727q"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"地球科学的研究对象主要包括：\n地球的固体部分（固体地球）、地球表面上下的水（水圈）、生态系统（生物圈）、大气层（大气圈）\n以及地球至太阳的行星际空间。使用物理方法研究地球的学科称为地球物理学，\n而固体地球物理学则是其中研究固体地球的分支学科。固体地球物理学的研究方法有很多，\n如遥感、GPS、重力、电磁、地震波、地热等，不同方法代表了不同专业方向。\n因此，从整个地球科学研究的角度来看，地震学只是一个\n很窄的专业方向，同时又是非常重要的研究手段。本章将介绍地震学的基础入门知识。","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"key":"kglwj6ZZyb"}],"key":"PonyW9SOb4"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"地震学是什么？","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"kSev3oCClZ"}],"identifier":"id","label":"地震学是什么？","html_id":"id","implicit":true,"key":"ULI96q11Qd"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Keiiti Aki 和 Paul G. Richards 编写的经典地震学教材《Quantitative Seismology》（第二版）","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"F3a6Ks8hCX"},{"type":"cite","kind":"narrative","label":"Aki2002","identifier":"aki2002","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Aki & Richards (2002)","key":"oW5gSHK1mJ"}],"enumerator":"1","key":"yZN7ojAnyZ"},{"type":"text","value":"\n对地震学的定义如下：","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"TqMxminrd8"}],"key":"egZ6RAEEEu"},{"type":"blockquote","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Seismology","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"key":"E98Dt725nR"}],"key":"LN3Heyu5Fk"},{"type":"text","value":" is the scientific study of mechanical vibrations of the Earth.\nQuantitative seismology is based on data called seismograms,\nwhich are recordings of the vibrations,\nwhich in turn may be caused artificially by man-made explosions,\nor caused naturally by earthquakes and volcanic eruptions.","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"key":"Mt0O1ddVck"}],"key":"p9P4HtdEi4"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"地震学是研究地球机械振动的科学。定量地震学基于记录着这些振动的观测资料，即地震图。\n这些振动可能是由人工爆炸等人为因素引起的，也可能是地震和火山喷发等自然活动造成的。","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"key":"SEmkaN7tBZ"}],"key":"R7Np8lAYRu"}],"key":"ddw3yMVupT"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":38,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"地震学是研究地球机械振动的科学。产生这些振动的源可能是地震、火山喷发、海浪、台风或飓风、\n人工爆炸、交通活动等，一般称为","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"key":"vAzIDBUx7o"},{"type":"link","url":"/seismology/seismic-source","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"震源","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"key":"gtoJPUsAeV"}],"key":"L7525cHAeD"}],"urlSource":"seismic-source.md","dataUrl":"/seismology.seismic-source.json","internal":true,"protocol":"file","key":"sIRXLvFTXV"},{"type":"text","value":"（seismic source），\n也常被称为","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"key":"e5w47sMSGz"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"地震事件","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"key":"cgAKTcMLTb"}],"key":"z1mn4PyfeH"},{"type":"text","value":"（seismic event）或","position":{"start":{"line":31,"